Great Hearts Academies plans to extend spring break at all of our campuses through the week of March 16th. There will be no regular school or after-school activities during this week. We plan to resume classes on March 23, 2020. You can stay informed on our website: https://www.greatheartsamerica.org/coronavirus/

Should we need to extend again, we will tell you as soon as we have made that decision.

We are very sorry for the inconveniences and hardships this may cause, but we sincerely believe it is in the best interest of our community at this time.

Great Hearts Academies
February 18 at 11:27 AM ¬∑

A school is its faculty.
Therefore, faculty talent is, and will always be, the most important element in the cultivation of our students.
To serve the teacher is to serve the student.
A teacher can only teach out who he or she is. When we look to faculty development, we look to the cultivation of the whole person. That could be providing a practical workshop or attending a Shakespearean play together.
Our job is to allow teachers to do this work they love for as long as they would love to do it ‚Äì to enable them to make a career out of their calling.
